However, if we do any of the above actions that might change the index of an item, despite that item remaining the same, you will get unexpected results.For example, if goats[2].name === 'Pygmy Goat' and we dispatch(actions.remove('goats', 1)), then goats[2].name === 'Booted Goat', which is not a desirable result.So what do we do?Model GettersModel getter functions answer the question, "What is the path to this entity?" especially if the path may change over time. It a function that:takes one argument: state (Object), which is the entire state tree of the store

and returns: model (String) - the string representation of the path to the model.

